{"title":"M0 PKPD FarmacoUPC iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica/M0 PKPD FarmacoUPC iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"M0 — PK/PD en el\\NAdulto Mayor Crítico","guid":"qPCO_zAsrh_rn2H7QUZqzQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Cambios Farmacocinéticos\\Ndel Envejecimiento","guid":"Y7FSCYHxvaHdyp_NMM3GMA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Absorción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"Difusión pasiva SIN CAMBIOS significativos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"↑ pH gástrico → ↓ absorción itraconazol, ketoconazol, Fe, Ca","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"↓ flujo esplácnico → ↑ biodisponibilidad fármacos alto clearance (propranolol, labetalol)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"2","text":"Efecto de primer paso hepático ↓ → ↑ F oral","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Distribución","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"↑ grasa corporal 35% → ↑ Vd LIPOFÍLICOS (diazepam, amiodarona) → ↑ t½","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"↓ agua corporal total 17% → ↓ Vd HIDROFÍLICOS (digoxina, litio) → ↑ Cp inicial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"7","text":"↓ líquido extracelular 40%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"7","text":"↓ masa magra → SARCOPENIA → sobreestima función renal con creatinina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"7","text":"↓ albúmina sérica → ↑ fracción libre fármacos ácidos (fenitoína, warfarina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"7","text":"↑ α1-glicoproteína ácida → ↓ fracción libre fármacos básicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"7","text":"En UCI: TERCER ESPACIO + edema → ↑↑ Vd hidrofílicos (ATB β-lactámicos, aminoglicósidos)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"1","text":"Metabolismo\\NHepático","guid":"7H6TS2YUBWHfds9D584nCw","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"↓ masa hepática 20-30%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"↓ flujo sanguíneo hepático 20-50%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"15","text":"Fase I\\N(CYP450)","guid":"bdLaGR7_R-IoBqHcUlYDiA","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"CYP3A4 → SIN CAMBIOS significativos con edad (dato in vitro + in vivo con midazolam)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"CYP2C19 → genotipo > edad como determinante (estudio omeprazol)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"CYP2D6 → genotipo es principal determinante (estudio paroxetina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"18","text":"↓ clearance hepático hasta 30% (antipirina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"18","text":"EN UCI: ↓↓ con hipoperfusión esplácnica + DVA → acumulación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"15","text":"Fase II\\N(conjugación)","guid":"TNLNuHzoO-pXNFXpD5_dFA","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"Glucuronidación, acetilación, sulfatación → PRESERVADAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"Inducción enzimática (rifampicina) → FUNCIONAL en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"15","text":"PERLA: genética (polimorfismos CYP) > edad como predictor de metabolismo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"28","parent":"1","text":"Eliminación\\NRenal","guid":"vCtf7szMiHV49S3rla-0Ew","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"↓ masa renal 20-30% entre 30-80 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"28","text":"PERO: 1/3 de AM NO tiene deterioro renal por edad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"28","text":"Comorbilidades (HTA, IC) > edad como causa de ↓ TFG","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"28","text":"CKD-EPI vs\\NCockcroft-Gault","guid":"p1zUKpmp60r8iROkPiXEkg","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"CKD-EPI preferida → CG subestima TFG","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"Cistatina C → mejor marcador que creatinina en AM (menos afectada por masa muscular)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"EN UCI: función renal FLUCTUANTE → medición directa CrCl 8h ideal","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"0","text":"Farmacocinética Alterada en UCI\\N(SOBRE envejecimiento)","guid":"_PHqlLC7g9DMApVmfkkRBQ","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"Volumen de Distribución\\NExpandido","guid":"KewC0cLU3B_ySH6iwGzFlw","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Hipoalbuminemia → ↑ fracción libre","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"Tercer espacio + edema → ↑↑ Vd hidrofílicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"Sarcopenia → ↓ reservorio muscular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"Fluidoterapia agresiva → dilución","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"37","text":"Implicancia: DOSIS DE CARGA AUMENTADAS para hidrofílicos (ATB)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"36","text":"Augmented\\NRenal Clearance\\N(ARC)","guid":"6_6f8T_dZ02eWIvswVcf7w","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"DEFINICIÓN: CrCl >130 mL/min/1.73m²","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"Prevalencia 14.9% en ≥60 años con sepsis (Zhou et al, JCPT 2020)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"43","text":"Prevalencia general UCI: 28-65%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"43","text":"Mecanismo: estado hiperdinámico → ↑ TFG, ↑ secreción tubular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"43","text":"Factores de riesgo en AM: ↑ BMI (OR 1.42), ↓ creatinina sérica (OR 0.88)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"43","text":"CONSECUENCIA: subdosificación ATB hidrofílicos → falla terapéutica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"43","text":"ARC + falla ATB: 27.3% vs 12.9% (Claus et al, p=0.04)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"43","text":"Detección: CrCl medido 8h (fórmulas subestiman en ARC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"43","text":"Manejo: ↑ dosis o ↓ intervalo + infusión prolongada β-lactámicos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"36","text":"Clearance\\NDisminuido","guid":"e0giaCsqKYcNZU4xyPPbnQ","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"Falla renal aguda → ↓ eliminación → acumulación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"Hipoperfusión hepática → ↓ metabolismo fase I","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"Disfunción multiorgánica → ↓↓ clearance global","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"53","text":"Implicancia: TDM OBLIGATORIO en fármacos de rango estrecho","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"36","text":"Función Renal\\NFluctuante","guid":"5ldvtcK_IzAwmOmrOfkeaw","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"Sepsis: ARC fase hiperdinámica → AKI fase tardía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"TRANSICIÓN puede ser rápida → ajustar dosis cada 24-48h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"CrCl medido > fórmulas estimadas en UCI","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"0","text":"Farmacodinamia en el AM Crítico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"↑ Sensibilidad a BZD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"Menor EC50 para sedación (midazolam) → efecto farmacodinámico, no PK","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"EVITAR en AM: delirium, acumulación, depresión respiratoria","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"↑ Sensibilidad a Opioides","guid":"","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"↓ requerimientos 30-50% vs joven","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"66","text":"Metabolitos activos (M6G morfina) → acumulación en IR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"62","text":"↑ Sensibilidad a Anticolinérgicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Carga anticolinérgica → delirium, retención urinaria, constipación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"Revisar STOPP/START al ingreso UCI","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"62","text":"↓ Respuesta β-Adrenérgica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"↓ densidad receptores β1/β2 con edad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"Mayor requerimiento de catecolaminas en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"Menor respuesta cronotrópica → esmolol puede ser más potente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"62","text":"↓ Respuesta Barorrefleja","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"Mayor susceptibilidad a hipotensión ortostática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"Hipotensión con cambios posturales en UCI","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"0","text":"Polifarmacia en UCI","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":">30 medicamentos por admisión promedio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"Interacciones fármaco-fármaco como REGLA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"Reconciliación medicamentosa al ingreso → OBLIGATORIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"79","text":"Deprescribir fármacos ambulatorios no esenciales en UCI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"79","text":"Revisar carga anticolinérgica (Anticholinergic Burden Scale)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"79","text":"STOPP/START adaptados a contexto crítico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"0","text":"Medicina de Precisión en UCI","guid":"","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Dosis de poblaciones ambulatorias NO son adecuadas en UCI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"Dosificación individualizada → PK poblacional + bayesiana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"TDM (Monitorización Terapéutica de Fármacos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Vancomicina: AUC/MIC target 400-600","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"Aminoglicósidos: Cmax/MIC ≥8-10","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"Antiepilépticos: niveles plasmáticos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"Digoxina: rango estrecho","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"94","parent":"86","text":"Biomarcadores de respuesta","guid":"","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"Procalcitonina → stewardship ATB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"94","text":"Lactato → resucitación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"94","text":"BNP → insuficiencia cardíaca","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"86","text":"FUTURO: farmacogenómica + dosificación bayesiana en tiempo real","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"99","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"Sarcopenia → creatinina BAJA → sobreestima función renal → ARC infradiagnosticada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"Solo 47.1% AM con sepsis alcanza valle vancomicina ≥15 mg/L → TDM obligatorio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"99","text":"Dosis de carga ATB hidrofílicos: NO reducir en AM con sepsis (Vd expandido)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"99","text":"Genética > edad como determinante de metabolismo CYP → farmacogenómica relevante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"99","text":"Start low, go slow PERO en sepsis: go FAST con ATB (subdosificación mata)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"99","text":"Fase II hepática PRESERVADA → preferir fármacos con glucuronidación en falla hepática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"99","text":"Fragilidad (CFS ≥5) = principal modificador pronóstico, no la edad cronológica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"99","text":"ARC existe incluso en ≥60a (14.9%) → no asumir IR por edad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"→ M5 Antimicrobianos UCI (Farmacología UPC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"→ M2 Sedación Analgesia Delirium (Farmacología UPC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"→ M13 TRR y ECMO (Farmacología UPC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"108","text":"→ M14 Farmacogenómica TDM (Farmacología UPC)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"1. Klotz U. Pharmacokinetics and drug metabolism in the elderly. Drug Metab Rev. 2009;41(2):67-76.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"113","text":"2. Zhou Q et al. Individualized vancomycin in elderly with sepsis and ARC. J Clin Pharm Ther. 2020;46(2):447-453.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"113","text":"3. Udy AA et al. ARC as predictor of subtherapeutic β-lactam. Clin Pharmacokinet. 2010;49(1):1-16.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"113","text":"4. Roberts JA et al. Individualised antibiotic dosing for the critically ill. Lancet Infect Dis. 2014;14(6):498-509.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"113","text":"5. Cook AM, Hatton-Kolpek J. Augmented Renal Clearance. Pharmacotherapy. 2019;39(3):346-354.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"113","text":"6. Landersdorfer CB, Nation RL. Key challenges in antibiotic therapy for sepsis. Clin Pharmacol Ther. 2021;109(4):892-904.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"113","text":"7. Erstad BL. Critical Care Pharmacotherapy. 2nd ed. ACCP; 2022. Cap. 1-2.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"113","text":"8. Cambridge. Principles of Geriatric Critical Care. 2021. Cap. 3.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":121,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"M0 PKPD FarmacoUPC iPad","id":"